  "prompt": "If you call someone on whatsapp by mistake and instantly hang up, does it still give them a missed call notification?",
  "response": "Yes, if you call someone on WhatsApp and hang up instantly, it will still give them a missed call notification, provided the app successfully initiated the call.\n\nHere\u2019s how it works:  \n1. When you tap the call button, WhatsApp attempts to connect the call.  \n2. If the call starts to ring or even if it\u2019s just in the process of connecting, and you hang up, the other person will receive a missed call notification.  \n3. If you hang up *very* quickly (before the call has a chance to connect), there\u2019s a slight chance it might not register as a missed call, but this is rare.  \n\nSo, in most cases, the other person will see a missed call notification, even if you hung up immediately.",
